// Local Xcode build settings.
//
// This file is read by every build. It is *not* overwritten by `xcodegen
// generate`, so personal settings live here instead of in `project.yml`.
//
// Setup (once):
//   1. Copy this file to `Local.xcconfig` (already gitignored).
//   2. Set DEVELOPMENT_TEAM to your Apple Developer team ID, found in
//      Xcode → Settings → Accounts → your Apple ID → row at the bottom,
//      column "Team ID" (10 characters, e.g. ABC123XYZ4).
//   3. Re-run `xcodegen generate`. From now on the Team setting survives
//      regenerations.
//
// Leave DEVELOPMENT_TEAM empty to keep ad-hoc ("Sign to Run Locally")
// signing — note that ad-hoc signatures change at every rebuild, which
// causes macOS to revoke previously-granted Accessibility permissions.

// DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = ABC123XYZ4
